doug8888



Atlanta, Georgia





Level 5  Contributor 


97 reviews 


15 hotel reviews





38 helpful votes 





“Avoid this hotel”


Reviewed May 19, 2017




This is a cheap hotel, in the worst sense of the term. It is ill equipped and uncomfortable. There is no room cleaning service, no hairdryer, no coffeemaker, the rooms have a kitchen however no utensils, cups.... you have to request everything from the front desk. We did request a coffee maker however this was an ancient machine that belonged in a garage sale.The bathroom fan was tremendously noisy and long overdue for replacement.While we were there they were changing out the room furniture and the replacements were dusty.The hotel is located right next to (feet away from) a railway line that carries heavy freight trainsThe hotel has a "grab and go" breakfast buffet, which basically comprises a couple of pots of coffee, some granola bars and prepackaged muffinsAll this for $250 per night (inc tax) !!


Room Tip: Find a room in a different hotel
See more room tips





Stayed May 2017, traveled on business



Location



Sleep Quality





Service






Helpful? 


Thank doug8888 





Report 




Ask doug8888 about Extended Stay America - San Jose - Santa Clara



This review is the subjective opinion of a TripAdvisor member and not of TripAdvisor LLC. 


00esa, General Manager at Extended Stay America - San Jose - Santa Clara, responded to this review,
May 20, 2017


We sincerely apologize for your disappointing stay. Please know, our housekeeping service is designed for long-term guests, offering minimal intrusion to their home-like stay, but we are happy to offer this service to you at a minimal fee. Our guests often bring their own bath amenities such as hairdryers and toiletries, so that's why these items are available at the front desk. Kitchenware for your suite is also available there. We are sorry if we didn’t communicate this to you during check-in. We value your feedback and will use it to ensure we are more consistent in our service levels. We regret the inconvenience caused and hope you will consider giving us another chance on your next trip to the area.Sincerely,General Manager



Report response as inappropriate

Thank you. We appreciate your input.


This response is the subjective opinion of the management representative and not of TripAdvisor LLC.







