Leaving_Samsara



Hampton, Virginia





Level 6  Contributor 


35 reviews 


4 hotel reviews





3 helpful votes 





“Surprise Backup”


Reviewed March 14, 2017




After my third-party booking site overbooked my stay at the Aloft Santa Clara, the staff at Aloft arranged for a very pleasant stay at the Extended Stay America. Check-in and checkout was simple and my room was on the second floor. For a budget hotel, everything was pretty top-notch. Absolutely no dirt, insects, or filth of any kind. Room comes standard with a kitchenette and a huge refrigerator. Bathroom was well stocked and clean. Bed not the best in the world, but comfortable enough for a good night's sleep. No hair or foreign substances anywhere! Extended Stay will never be my first choice, but for my first hotel providing excellent customer service they did not do bad all! Train noise in the night is out of control. I usually wear ear plugs at night and that noise easily broke through my silicone barriers. I wasn't sleep at the time, but I imagine if I were I'd be awakened immediately. If you're a light sleeper, this isn't the place for you.





Stayed March 2017, traveled solo



Value





Rooms



Service






