Anita W



Orcutt, California





Level 4  Contributor 


32 reviews 


9 hotel reviews





16 helpful votes 





“Better than Expected...”


Reviewed May 22, 2017




My girlfriend and I stayed at this hotel while seeing a concert at Levi Stadium. It was the only hotel within walking distance of the stadium that was still available at the time of our booking. We weren't too excited, but the hotel staff was eager to please and took care of our check-in and had us in our room quickly. We had no issues, and the coffee and "to go" breakfast was appreciated. Completely adequate for our needs.


Room Tip: Higher floors were quieter.
See more room tips





Stayed May 2017, traveled with friends



